Mass:
Definition:
Mass is a fundamental property of an object, representing the amount of matter it contains. 
Measurement:
It's measured in kilograms (kg) in the International System of Units (SI). 
Inertia:
Mass is also a measure of an object's resistance to changes in its motion, known as inertia. 
Constant:
An object's mass remains constant regardless of its location or the gravitational force acting upon it. 
Weight:
Definition:
Weight is the force of gravity acting on an object's mass. 
Measurement:
